Implementation
Step 1: Configure AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}
Step 2: Create EBS Volume
resource "aws_ebs_volume" "devops_volume" {
  availability_zone = "us-east-1a"
  size              = 10
  type              = "gp2"

  tags = {
    Name = "devops-ebs-volume"
  }
}
Explanation
availability_zone
availability_zone = "us-east-1a"

EBS volumes are AZ-specific, meaning they must be created in the same availability zone as the EC2 instance they will attach to.

size
size = 10

Defines the storage capacity in GB.

type
type = "gp2"

Specifies the volume type:

Type	Description
gp2	General Purpose SSD
gp3	Newer SSD (recommended)
io1/io2	High-performance workloads
sc1	Cold HDD
st1	Throughput optimized HDD
Step 3: Initialize Terraform
terraform init
Step 4: Validate Configuration
terraform validate
Step 5: Preview Changes
terraform plan
Step 6: Apply Configuration
terraform apply

Confirm:

yes
Step 7: Verify Deployment
terraform state list

